  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-03 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. A requirement binds experimental-validation as the required verification method; however, the supporting validation activity is a literature-review of published hemolysis correlations, which the narrative presents as a complementary evidence source sufficient to satisfy the requirement. The structured fields disagree: the requirement mandates experimental-validation, but the activity that generated the primary ValidationResult carries activityType literature-review.",
