    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/cou2-vad-decision",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-lead-assessor",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The assessment team concluded that the literature-review evidence, covering 17 published hemolysis datasets with mean deviation of 12.4%, provides sufficient corroborating support for the hemolysis model. The review was judged to demonstrate broad consistency between the CFD model's constitutive assumptions and the published scientific record. On this basis the team accepted the credibility claim, noting that the literature survey comprehensively covers the relevant operating envelope. No reference to the requirement for experimental-validation against physical bench measurements was made in the decision deliberations.",
